# Windsurf Rules — nullprobe

## What this project is

nullprobe: Deep-void probe that deploys living, self-updating procedural memory, principles, guardrails, and skills before every mission.

## Session Start

Read `docs/CONTEXT.md` first — current status, key files, recent changes.
Read `AGENTS.md` for the multi-environment setup overview.

## Source Architecture

`src/index.ts` → commands → flows (inquirer) → scaffolder → templates (string constants)

**Critical:** When adding a new skill template in `src/scaffolder/templates/`, you must also add it to the `files` array in `src/scaffolder/index.ts` or it will never be written.

## Multi-Environment Namespaces

This project runs Claude Code, Cursor, Antigravity, and Windsurf in parallel.
Each owns its config directory — don't edit other namespaces unless updating shared protocols.
Shared territory: `src/`, `AI_FRAMEWORK.md`, `wiki/`, `docs/CONTEXT.md`

## Build Check

`npm run build` must pass before finishing any work. TypeScript strict mode, ESM-only.

## Behavioral Guidelines (Karpathy)

- Think Before Coding — state assumptions, surface tradeoffs
- Simplicity First — no speculative features or abstractions
- Surgical Changes — every changed line traces to the request
- Goal-Driven Execution — verifiable success criteria per step

## Core Principle

Lightweight above all. If a feature makes the tool more complex to use, it doesn't belong.
